<title type="html"><![CDATA[3/13(Sat.)Compliments You Didn’t Realize Are Pretty Insulting/New Super-Enzyme Can Break Down Plastic...(Vincent)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=480&amp;p=502#p502"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">3/13(Sat.) Some Compliments You Didn’t Realize Are Actually Pretty Insulting/New Super-Enzyme Can Break Down Plastic at Rapid Pace(Host:Vincent)</span><br /><br />Article1:Some Compliments You Didn’t Realize Are Actually Pretty Insulting<br />Link: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1opTS4K5FY34IxyWu5qBM09LfmAXWGp0z/view?usp=sharing" class="postlink">https://drive.google.com/file/d/1opTS4K5FY34IxyWu5qBM09LfmAXWGp0z/view?usp=sharing</a><br />1.backhanded: a. 隱含譏刺的<br />2.compliment: n. 讚美的話<br />3.perpetuate: v. 使永久存在<br />4.condescending: a. 有優越感的<br />5.elaborate: v. 詳盡闡述<br />6.tantrum: n. 發脾氣<br />7.platitude: n. 陳詞濫調<br />8.adequate: a. 勝任的<br />9.nauseating: a. 使人厭惡的<br />10.articulate: a. 發音清晰的<br />11.acquaintance: n. 相識的人<br />12.wizened: a. 面孔乾瘦的<br />13.crone: n. 醜老太婆<br />14.spinster: n. 未婚女子<br />15.buck up: 振作<br />16.grump: n. 脾氣壞的人<br />17.unsolicited: a. 未經請求的<br />18.devastating: a. 辛辣的，挖苦的<br /><br />Discussion questions<br />1.Why are some compliments considered actually insulting? Do they have common factors?<br />2.What are some other examples of “insulting” compliments?<br />3.Has anybody you know been given “insulting” complements? Or have you given one to your friend? How does the person deal with this embarrassing moment?<br />4.Please think up some ways or smart lines to answer to the above mentioned “insulting” compliments or give some suggestions to avoid embarrassing moments.<br /><br /><br />///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////<br />Artilce2:New Super-Enzyme Can Break Down Plastic at Rapid Pace<br />Link:<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1tbTcJ88CsUnbhElWZQSzSM1CMUurfLzn/view?usp=sharing" class="postlink">https://drive.google.com/file/d/1tbTcJ88CsUnbhElWZQSzSM1CMUurfLzn/view?usp=sharing</a><br /><br /><br />Glossary<br />1.enzyme: n. 酵素<br />2.degrade: v. 分解<br />3.incinerate: v. 焚化<br />4.contaminate: v. 汙染；毒害<br />5.constituent: n. 成分<br />6.trajectory: n. 軌跡<br />7.compost: n. 堆肥<br />8.crystalline: a. 結晶的；透明的；<br />9.cellulose: n. 纖維素；（植物的）細胞膜質<br />10.molecule: n. 分子<br />11.tweak: v. 扭；捏；擰<br />12.polyurethane: n. 聚氨酯<br /><br /><br /><br />Discussion questions<br />1. Are you worried about climate change? Which part of it do you think is the most serious one?<br />2. Do you do recycling in your daily life? If yes, how do you do that? If not, what do you do think you can do to be the first step?<br />3. Do you think the super-enzyme will really solve the problem of using plastic? Besides it, do you know any other new technology that helps protect our earth?<br /><br /><br />///////////////////////////////////////////////////////<br />Agenda<br />7:00 ~ 7:30 pm greetings &amp; free talk<br />7:30 ~ 8:15 pm guests introduced &amp; first session discussion<br />8:15 ~ 8:45 pm presentation, sharing the article &amp; other experiences<br />8:45 ~ 9:30 pm second session discussion<br /><br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven,<br />板橋民生路二段237 號,<br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30,<br /><br />P.S.<br />1.因聚會地點是在咖啡店內，所以有低消80元喔！<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交1000元 (學生:500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Wed Mar 10, 2021 11:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
